    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1954-07-16T15:30:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1954-07-16T15:30:00-05:00" n="125"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d125">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">460.509/7–1654: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Embassy in the United Kingdom</gloss>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d125fn1">This telegram, drafted by Goodkind and cleared by
                        Roderic O’Connor, was repeated to Paris.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                        <lb/>
                        <gloss target="#t_niact1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">niact</hi>
                        </gloss>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1954-07-16T16:30:00-04:00"
                            >July 16, 1954—4:30 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>327. <gloss target="#t_Excon1">Excon</gloss>. For Stassen from Dulles. Regarding
                    timing for implementing decontrol items in my view the situation upon which the
                        <gloss target="#t_NSC1">NSC</gloss> decision was based remains the same. I
                    believe that actual decontrol should be deferred and that the situation at
                    Geneva is such that we can set no definite future date. Recognize British may
                    react strongly against our position but we would be subject here to heavy
                    criticism if we make concessions on this issue prior to a definitive result at
                    Geneva. This would appear to be giving away our trump card before the game had
                    started. If you feel our position will result in serious breach with British in
                        <gloss target="#t_CG1">CG</gloss> meeting we can discuss matter further on
                    your return.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Dulles</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
